{"title": "Pyrotechnics: The History and Art of Firework Making", "description": "Captain St. Hill Brock presents here, in Part I, a brief history of pyrotechnics from origins in the East through the present.  Part II delves more into a description of the fireworks themselves, there manufacture, and some modern uses, and a tribute to his brother, Wing-Commander Frank Arthur Brock, R.N.A.S. Killed at Zeebrugge April 23rd, 1918.  From his introduction: \u201cMy object has not been to write a text-book on firework-making, but rather to trace the art from earliest times, and to give a description of the development and process of manufacture. . . . My excuse for adding another volume to the literature of the art is that I am of the eighth generation of a family of pyrotechnists, whose work, I venture to claim, has not been without its effect.\u201d - Summary by Larry Wilson", "duration": 21449, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "17367", "name": "Alan St. Hill Brock"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/pyrotechnics_2304_librivox/pyrotechnics_2304.jpg", "copyright_year": "1922", "genres": ["Technology & Engineering"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Larry Wilson"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Amy Gramour"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "James R. Hedrick"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Dediction and Introduction", "readers": [8425], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/pyrotechnics_2304_librivox/pyrotechnics_00_brock_64kb.mp3", "duration": 341}, {"section": 1, "title": "The Origin of Pyrotechny", "readers": [8425], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/pyrotechnics_2304_librivox/pyrotechnics_01_brock_64kb.mp3", "duration": 329}, {"section": 2, "title": "Pyrotechny in the East", "readers": [14309], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/pyrotechnics_2304_librivox/pyrotechnics_02_brock_64kb.mp3", "duration": 739}, {"section": 3, "title": "Pyrotechny